values.performance: The student is doing really well.  She is a pleasure to have in the clinic. She is a super-quick learner and very motivated to learn. she is doing parts of treatment sessions and co-treatment for evaluations. She is independent with clinical reasoning.

values.education: Things have been going really well. Able to apply what she has learned in the classroom. Starting to take patients on her own. Seeing ortho, has 2 CRPS- Clinical has been really eye-opening - all different exercises, how to progress and regress exercises and how different patients with the same diagnosis present. first eval was a patient with a distal tib fracture with fibromyalgia and very deconditioned.  Difficult donning and doffing boot and very limited ankle range after being immobilized. The CI is supportive, checks in several times per day  - does not hover and asks questions to help her learn.  Has shown her how to do Graston.

values.strengths: Professionalism, initiative takes an active role in her learning, completing the subjective portion of the eval and knowing when to cut the patient off if on a tangent, documentation
values.Goals: Progression/regression of program, communicating with patients who do not speak English, understanding how psychosocial factors impact delivery of care, nuances of billing, diagnosing movement versus specific condition, delegating to PTA
values.caseload:
50% - 5-6 patients per day including evals
New Grad: 10-12

values.Comments1: Student: felt prepared didactically. Would benefit from more in person ICE versus remote - to get more experience speaking to patients
values.Comments2: Feel 10 weeks is good in this setting.
values.Comments3: Last one should be longer to allow the student more time to be practicing as a PT prior to graduation
values.ci4: There are good and bad of both - good - you have all the coursework, bad - the expectations of CI for backended student is higher because the had all didactic.  Sees the benfit of both.
values.Student4: Keep as is - likes to practice skills just learned

values.Comments3:

CI is excellent - great communication, great teacher, she allows the student the opportunity to practice skills without being over-protective.

values.performance: Things have been great. Taking a hand full of patients every day. Given a list of patient for the day, develops a plan and writes the notes. Practicing a lot of clinical reasoning and evals daily.
values.safety: occasional issues with body mechanics but responds well to feedback
values.communication: CI and student a lot throughout the day
values.professionalism: excellent - always prepared ahead of time and open to learning

values.education: Clinical going well. Likes her clinical. Seeing a lot of patients with LBP, post-op TKR, ORIF, shoulder and vertigo. CI is great and getting enough supervision and feedback. Learning a lot  - always talking about patients, treatment, ways to improve skills.

values.strengths:
Professionalism - positive attitude, willingness to learn and try new things, accepts and implements feedback well, understands strengths and limitations
Communication - written and oral
Subjective portion of eval - MMT/goals
Focus on quality of care - able to adapt to patient response
Manual techniques - goni and MMT are spot on!
values.Goals:
Billing/documentation (nuances between codes, ST/LTG)
Continue to work on clinical reasoning
Speak to patient in layman's/confidence
Learning more about socioeconomic status/psychosocial impact on care

values.performance: Student is doing well. Acclimating to the facility - doing patient treatments, some documentation and portions of the eval.
values.professionalism: Student is always professional - no issues

values.education: Clinical is gowing well. Learning how to be more efficient and determine the best questions to ask, best tests to utilize. CI taking it slow - talks things through. Excellent communication with CI and the right amount of feedback and supervision. Doing MMT, Special tests, history, getting to the point of almost doing a full eval and follow -up visits.  Learning a lot - especially time management. No concerns at this time

values.strengths: Professionalism - EL - solicits and accepts feedback well. Understands when things are outside of her comfort zone or scope of practice. She treats all patients respectfully.  Uses EBP and CPG to guide patient treatment. She is able to collect and synthesize information from the evaluations and treatment and progress and regress treatment plans accordingly. Doing well with documentation and completes it in a timely manner.  Understands billing procedures.
values.Goals:
Work on making explanations more concise
Streamline assessments
Wording of goals
Time management - staying on schedule with pt care
Practice more hands on skills
values.caseload: 50% of the caseload - supervision depends on the complexity of the patients and varies day to day. Needs full supervision with evals.

values.Student4: Keep as is - likes to practice skills just learned

values.Comments3: Overall is an excellent experience. Students only concern is that she needs more space during evals - CI quick to jump in and take over if they identify something the student did not ask or assess. Discussed this with the CI and recommended she let the student complete the eval and unless there is a safety concern, to add to the eval at the end of the evaluation to see if student eventually gets there on their own.

values.performance: Student is doing well. Was a little shy at first, but coming out of her shell.  She is doing portions of treatments, subjective portion of the evaluations and documentation. She accepts feedback well and implements it accordingly. Eager to learn and connects well with patients

values.education: Initially it was chaotic with not much orientation when she started due to staffing. Second and third week are going much better and now Enjoying the clinical and learning a lot. Doing treatments and parts of the eval. Learning the documentation system and billing. CI has been great - open communication, talk a lot throughout the day, supervision is good and no concerns at this time.

values.strengths: * CI did not complete the CPI; however, the CI, Student and SCCE discussed each criteria. Student will be graded at the advanced beginner level. She is very professional, takes feedback well, has identified areas of concern (i.e. PTA doing treatments that were d/c by the PT) and learning how to handle them in a tactful manner.  The complexity of the caseload has been high and although ortho, patients have many co-morbidities as well as neuro issues in addition to ortho issues. The student comes to the clinic prepared, takes feedback well and integrates it. She knows her limitations and is not afraid to ask for help. She treats all patients with dignity and respect and is mindful of psychosocial issues that impact care. She is slowly building a caseload. Evals - doing all parts and learning to streamline and determine which special tests to perform (sometimes does too many). Treatments are going well and practicing manual skills.
values.Goals:
Be able to select the best special tests to do during eval
Improve goal writing
Improve proficiency with non-complex and complex patients
Time management

values.Comments3: CI and student feel all clincials should be 12 weeks
Great place to be - alot of variety of patients and levels of complexity - gen ortho to post op to both with multiple medical issues

values.performance: Josiah is doing an excellent job.  He is professional and always comes in ready to work and learn. He is not afraid to ask questions and takes feedback well. He has seen a number of patients of varying complexity on the inpatient acute care unit. Being a student at RI Hospital, the CI gets to cherry pick the new evals the student is exposed to. No issues with any red flag areas - just working on typical inpatient acute care - setting up the environment and getting comfortable responding to changes in medical status
values.safety: no - just working on setting up the environment

values.education: Student reported he is enjoying his clinical. He is taking on more evals and treats on his own and doing documentation. He is completing the subjective section of evals. Notes him and his CI work well and the CI provides effective feedback as needed.  No concerns at this time.

values.strengths: Professionalism - he understands his strengths and weaknesses.  He understands when potential unprofessional behaviors and challenging ethical situations arise. He is a proactive learner - just attended RI burn center meeting. He is able to take feedback without defensiveness and implement it and is able to provide his CI with feedback as well. He has effective verbal and non verbal communication.  Recognizes socioeconomic, psychological influences on care  All ratings between an Intermediate and Advanced intermediate.
values.Goals:
research diagnoses/EBP/objective measures for acute care setting
determine when to refer to another service when indicated
discuss POC/disposition with other HCP
Complex patients
More confident with discharge disposition and independence with chart review
